div.p:
WHosoever make a voluntary separation of themselves
from the whole, true, visible Church of Christ,
are Schismatiques;

Whosoever either Possess the Sees and Offices of lawful


Bishops, those lawful Bishops yet living, or unite themselves
to such as possess them, are such schismatical Pastors;

Whosoever were once lawful Bishops, and never did any
thing after, whereby they became unlawful, remained still
lawful Bishops;

No National Church can be a true particular Church of
Christ, unless those who have the place of Bishops in it be
lawful Bishops;

If those lawful Bishops did any thing, whereby they became
unlawful Bishops, it must be supposed to be that for
which they were deprived;

No proceeding in practice, according to the common
Tenets, the holding whereof made them not unlawful Bishops,
can make them unlawful Bishops;
